{"body": "<div class=\"section\" id=\"how-to-create-an-index-list-with-index-terms\">\n<h1>How to create an index list with index terms<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#how-to-create-an-index-list-with-index-terms\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h1>\n<p>Produce &amp; Publish provides a simple build-in mechanism for generating a list\nof index terms with their occurrence (page-numbers).</p>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"prequisites\">\n<h2>Prequisites<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#prequisites\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>All index terms must be marked using:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-python\"><pre>&lt;span class=\"index-term\"&gt;some index term&lt;/span&gt;</pre>\n</div>\n<p>This can either be accomplished by generating the related markup through the\ncontent-type specific browser views/templates that are registered as\n<tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">&#64;&#64;asHTML</span></tt> view (Produce &amp; Publish Plone Client Connector) or you highlight a\nterm inside TinyMCE and apply the style <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">Index</span> <span class=\"pre\">term</span></tt> from the styles dropdown\nmenu (Produce &amp; Publish Authoring Environment).</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"generating-an-index-through-the-plone-client-connector\">\n<h2>Generating an index through the Plone Client Connector<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#generating-an-index-through-the-plone-client-connector\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>The standard <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">&#64;&#64;asPlainPDF</span></tt> view of the Plone Client Connector will\nautomatically create an index listing at the end of the document. The\nunderlaying transformation <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">addIndexList</span></tt> is called automatically (see\n<tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">pdf.py</span></tt> file within the client connector sources)</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"generating-an-index-through-the-authoring-environment\">\n<h2>Generating an index through the Authoring Environment<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#generating-an-index-through-the-authoring-environment\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>Inside the Authoring Environment have the option to create individual listings\nincluding an index listing by checking the related checkbox from the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">PDF</span></tt>\ntab of your conversions page.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"custom-location-of-the-indexes-listing-inside-your-template\">\n<h2>Custom location of the indexes listing inside your template<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#custom-location-of-the-indexes-listing-inside-your-template\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>By default the index listing will be added to the end of the document. However you can\ncontrol the place through a custom PDF rendering template (e.g. inside your own\nresources directory). You may place the following markup e.g. in front or after the body\ntext:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-python\"><pre>&lt;div id=\"indexes-list\"&gt;\n    index listing will be inserted here\n&lt;/div&gt;</pre>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n", "display_toc": true, "title": "How to create an index list with index terms", "sourcename": "howto/index-listing.txt", "customsidebar": null, "current_page_name": "howto/index-listing", "next": {"link": "../../misc/download-servers/", "title": "Download servers"}, "rellinks": [["genindex", "General Index", "I", "index"], ["misc/download-servers", "Download servers", "N", "next"], ["howto/s5-customization", "Customizing S5 templates and styles (Authoring Environment)", "P", "previous"]], "meta": {}, "parents": [], "sidebars": null, "toc": "<ul>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#\">How to create an index list with index terms</a><ul>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#prequisites\">Prequisites</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#generating-an-index-through-the-plone-client-connector\">Generating an index through the Plone Client Connector</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#generating-an-index-through-the-authoring-environment\">Generating an index through the Authoring Environment</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#custom-location-of-the-indexes-listing-inside-your-template\">Custom location of the indexes listing inside your template</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n", "prev": {"link": "../s5-customization/", "title": "Customizing S5 templates and styles (Authoring Environment)"}, "metatags": ""}